The paper is about conversational question answering models in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of datasets and training settings, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also analyzes the models' capability of content understanding, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
